{#
  ShareChooser macro — glyph button that opens the native share sheet
  where the browser has one, and otherwise a disclosure list of
  consumer-supplied destinations plus a copy-the-URL action.

  HTML tag: <div> (root), <button> + <ul> (disclosure, NOT a menu)
  CSS class: share-chooser
  Companion runtime: share-chooser.client.js

  This is the first helper in the catalog that owns an ACTION rather
  than a user preference. It applies nothing to the document and
  persists nothing: no localStorage, no data-* on the document root.

  ---------------------------------------------------------------------
  NUNJUCKS DEVIATION — `href` is a STRING here, not a function
  ---------------------------------------------------------------------

  The canonical Svelte helper types a target's `href` as
  `(url, title, text) => string`, so the consumer owns the whole URL and
  no endpoint convention is baked in. A Nunjucks macro cannot call an
  arbitrary JavaScript function: templates may only call filters and
  globals that the consumer has registered on the environment, so a
  function passed through `opts` would render as the empty string.

  Therefore the macro takes each target's `href` as an ALREADY-RESOLVED
  string. This costs the consumer nothing they were not already doing —
  they are building the page server-side and already hold the url, title
  and text — and it keeps the server output honest: the anchors carry
  real, final hrefs, which is what makes the no-JS story work (see
  docs/ssr.md).

  The function-based API survives on the client, where functions are
  callable: pass `targets` with function `href`s to
  `initShareChooser(root, {targets})` and the client re-resolves every
  anchor's href from the live URL. See spec/index.md §3.3.

  Params (single `opts` object):
    label       — string, required. aria-label for the trigger button.
                  The button is glyph-only, so this is the ONLY
                  accessible name it has.
    targets     — array of objects, each:
                    id      — string, required. Passed back to onShare.
                    label   — string, required. Visible link text.
                    href    — string, required. The FULL destination URL,
                              already built by the consumer. See the
                              deviation note above.
                    newTab  — boolean, default true. False renders the
                              link without target="_blank".
    url         — string. The URL to share. Emitted as
                  data-lily-share-chooser-url for the client; when unset
                  the client falls back to location.href at share time.
    title       — string. Passed to the native share sheet.
    text        — string. Passed to the native share sheet.
    copyLabel   — string. The copy item renders ONLY when this is
                  supplied — there is no default, because a default
                  would be a hardcoded English string.
    copiedLabel — string. Announced in the status region after a
                  successful copy.
    copyFailedLabel — string. Announced when the clipboard write fails.
    strategy    — "auto" | "native" | "list", default "auto".
    name        — string, default "share". Discriminator used to derive
                  ids.
    id          — string. Id prefix for the list and its items.
                  Defaults to "share-chooser-{name}". Supply an explicit
                  id when rendering two instances that share a `name`.
    classes     — string. Extra CSS classes on the root <div>.
    attributes  — object. Extra HTML attributes spread onto the root.

  Custom glyph: call the macro with a `{% call %}` block and the block
  body replaces the default glyph inside the button:

    {% call shareChooser({label: "Share", targets: [...]}) %}
      <svg aria-hidden="true">…</svg>
    {% endcall %}

  Usage:
    {% from "./share-chooser.njk" import shareChooser %}
    {{ shareChooser({
      label: "Share this page",
      url: page.url,
      targets: [
        {id: "mastodon", label: "Mastodon", href: mastodonHref},
        {id: "email", label: "Email", href: mailtoHref, newTab: false}
      ],
      copyLabel: "Copy link",
      copiedLabel: "Link copied",
      copyFailedLabel: "Could not copy — copy it from the address bar"
    }) }}

  Then load share-chooser.client.js once and call autoInit().

  NOTE: the destination links WORK without JavaScript — they are real
  hrefs — but the list cannot be opened and copy does not function. See
  docs/ssr.md.

  NO SOCIAL-NETWORK ENDPOINTS SHIP WITH THIS PACKAGE. Which networks
  exist is an editorial and privacy decision belonging to the consumer,
  and share URLs change.

  Spec: spec/index.md §4.1 (macro parameters), §4.2 (DOM contract).
#}
{%- macro shareChooser(opts) -%}
{%- set name = opts.name | default("share") -%}
{%- set id = opts.id | default("share-chooser-" + name) -%}
{%- set listId = id + "-list" -%}
{%- set strategy = opts.strategy | default("auto") -%}
{%- set targets = opts.targets | default([]) -%}
<div
  class="share-chooser{% if opts.classes %} {{ opts.classes }}{% endif %}"
  data-lily-share-chooser-root
  data-lily-share-chooser-name="{{ name }}"
  data-lily-share-chooser-strategy="{{ strategy }}"
  {%- if opts.url %} data-lily-share-chooser-url="{{ opts.url }}"{% endif %}
  {%- if opts.title %} data-lily-share-chooser-title="{{ opts.title }}"{% endif %}
  {%- if opts.text %} data-lily-share-chooser-text="{{ opts.text }}"{% endif %}
  {%- if opts.copiedLabel %} data-lily-share-chooser-copied-label="{{ opts.copiedLabel }}"{% endif %}
  {%- if opts.copyFailedLabel %} data-lily-share-chooser-copy-failed-label="{{ opts.copyFailedLabel }}"{% endif %}
  {%- if opts.attributes %}{% for k, v in opts.attributes %} {{ k }}="{{ v }}"{% endfor %}{% endif %}
>
<button type="button" class="share-chooser-button" aria-label="{{ opts.label }}" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="{{ listId }}" data-lily-share-chooser-button>
{%- if caller %}{{ caller() }}{% else %}<span class="share-chooser-icon" aria-hidden="true">&#8618;</span>{% endif -%}
</button>
<ul class="share-chooser-list" id="{{ listId }}" hidden data-lily-share-chooser-list>
{%- for target in targets -%}
  {#- A real link, not role="menuitem": these ARE navigation, and
      menuitem would strip middle-click, open-in-new-tab and
      copy-link-address. No role override is emitted, deliberately. -#}
  <li class="share-chooser-list-item">
    <a class="share-chooser-target" id="{{ id }}-target-{{ loop.index0 }}" data-target-id="{{ target.id }}" href="{{ target.href }}"{% if target.newTab !== false %} target="_blank"{% endif %} rel="noopener noreferrer">{{ target.label }}</a>
  </li>
{%- endfor -%}
{%- if opts.copyLabel -%}
  <li class="share-chooser-list-item">
    <button type="button" class="share-chooser-copy" id="{{ id }}-copy" data-lily-share-chooser-copy>{{ opts.copyLabel }}</button>
  </li>
{%- endif -%}
</ul>
{#- Copying gives no visual feedback of its own, so the outcome is
    announced. Empty until something happens, so it stays silent on
    load; aria-live announces mutations only. -#}
<p class="share-chooser-status" aria-live="polite" data-lily-share-chooser-status></p>
</div>
{%- endmacro -%}
